Package com.backend.boilerplate.service

Interface AutoCompleteService<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Model class representing the type of auto complete service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CityAutoCompleteServiceImpl, StateAutoCompleteServiceImpl 
    public interface AutoCompleteService<T>
    Generic auto complete service which is responsible for getting search results for any component. Every service which is supposed to process auto complete search; should implement this interface. Every service must have its own Model class of type <T> so that service can process request for given key see search(String) and returns result as List of <T>

    Every implementing Spring Service must have unique Qualifier.

    AutoCompleteComponent must have mapping of type and it's service Qualifier.

    This type should be exactly same as PathVariable of search API.

    Author:
    sarvesh

    • Method Detail

      • search

        java.util.List<T> search​(java.lang.String key)
        Encapsulate core business logic of searching for a given key in database and returns the sorted result. Database Entity is queried for given key to get List list of DTO objects for specified Database Entity. This list of DTO objects is then copied to its related List<T> which is followed by sorting.

        Implementing service can have its custom Comparator for this sorting inside package com.backend.boilerplate.service.helper

        Result List<T> can be stored in cache against the requested key.

        Caching mechanism can be implemented using SynchronizedInMemoryCache which follows Least Recently Used algorithm in synchronized context

        Parameters:
        key - non-null keyword to search.
        Returns:
        List list of <T>

      • search

        java.util.List<T> search​(java.lang.String key,
                         java.lang.Integer maxResult)
        Encapsulate core business logic of searching for a given key in database and returns the sorted result. Database Entity is queried for given key to get List sorted list of DTO objects for specified Database Entity. This sorted list of DTO objects is then copied to its related List<T>.

        Result List<T> can be stored in cache against the requested key.

        Caching mechanism can be implemented using SynchronizedInMemoryCache which follows Least Recently Used algorithm in synchronized context

        Parameters:
        key - non-null keyword to search.
        maxResult - maximum number of suggestions needed
        Returns:
        List list of <T>
